  "prompt": "Will the YIF call for a telephonic interview on a day other than the given date?",
  "response": "The **Young India Fellowship (YIF)** typically provides specific dates for telephonic interviews as part of their selection process. However, if a candidate is unable to attend the interview on the given date due to a genuine conflict or unforeseen circumstances, it is advisable to contact the YIF admissions team **well in advance** to explain the situation. They may consider rescheduling the interview on a case-by-case basis, depending on their availability and the reason provided.\n\nIt\u2019s important to communicate proactively and professionally, as flexibility is not guaranteed. Always check the official YIF communication or website for any updates or guidelines regarding the interview process.",
